The '''Players Handbook 1st edition''', also known as '''Players Handbook''', is the Player's Handbook for the 1{{st}} edition of ''Advanced Dungeons & Dragons''.

From the January 1980 printing:
{{Quote|''"A wealth of information for the AD&D game player"|[[Gary Gygax]], creator of the AD&D<sup>&reg;</sup> game phenomenon and author of this book.''}}

{{Quote|'''''This is it!''' It's the perfect player's game-playing aid and the best companion to the referee's [[Dungeon Masters Guide 1st edition|Dungeon Masters Guide]]. As a player, this handbook will help you determine your character's abilities such as strength, wisdom and charisma. Character races including [[elves]], [[halfling]]s, [[dwarves]], [[gnome]]s and others are explained in detail to make the adventure fast, fun and exciting. You'll learn the rules for progressing in character levels and the most advantageous mapping and combat procedures. And they're all in this easy to use book.''}}
